- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper deals with the computational complexity of computing a distance measure between two models.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as hidden Markov models are commonly used in machine learning for sequence modeling and the paper deals with computing the distance between two such models.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with measuring the difference between two probability distributions.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the computational complexity of approximating the distance measure.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as hidden Markov models are also used in control theory and the paper deals with computing the distance between two such models.
